● UserContext Builder Assessment

  The UserContext builder exists and operates optimally. Here's the summary:

  Architecture Overview

  The builder was refactored in December 2025 (ADR-016) from a 2,102-line monolith into 4 focused modules:

  | File                      | Lines | Responsibility        |
  |---------------------------|-------|-----------------------|
  | user_context_builder.py   | 331   | Orchestration         |
  | user_context_queries.py   | 988   | MEGA-QUERY + executor |
  | user_context_extractor.py | 351   | Result parsing        |
  | user_context_populator.py | 235   | Context population    |
  | unified_user_context.py   | 920   | ~240 field dataclass  |

  Performance Optimizations

  Single MEGA-QUERY Architecture:
  - Old: 5-9 database round-trips
  - New: 1 round-trip fetches both UIDs and rich data
  - Result: 3-5x performance improvement

  Pure Python Extraction:
  - Graph-sourced relationships computed from already-fetched data
  - Zero additional database calls after initial query

  Caching Layer:
  - 5-minute TTL cache with invalidation on domain mutations

  Strengths

  1. Excellent separation of concerns - Query, extraction, and population isolated
  2. Type safety - Result[T] pattern, ~240 strongly-typed fields
  3. Single source of truth - ProfileHubData computed FROM context
  4. Eliminates N+1 - One comprehensive query vs many sequential

  Minor Optimization Opportunities

  | Opportunity                                         | Effort | Impact |
  |-----------------------------------------------------|--------|--------|
  | Query parameterization (fetch only needed sections) | Low    | Medium |
  | Collection size limits (power users)                | Low    | Low    |
  | Extraction parallelization                          | Medium | Low    |
  | Cache warming on login                              | Medium | Medium |

  Verdict

  Production-ready and well-maintained. No significant refactoring needed. This architecture serves as a template for other cross-domain context builders - it demonstrates SKUEL's philosophy of "core operators do the work" with comprehensive queries and pure function extraction.
